==Jamaican Creole==
===Etymology===
Possibly from or related to {{m|jam|nyanga}}, from {{der|jam|men|nyanga||ostentation; showing off}}.  Possibly influenced by {{cog|es|yanga||carelessly; without necessity}}.  Compare {{cog|bnt-pro|*-yȧng-||dance in joy}}<!-- source reads "cf CB [Common Bantu] *-yȧng-, dance about in joy" --> and {{cog|kg|-yangalala||be happy}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|jam|/ˈjaŋɡa/}}
===Noun===
{{jam-noun}}
# A [[dance]] with a [[fast]] [[rhythm]].
===Verb===
{{jam-verb}}
# To [[walk]] or [[dance]] [[provocatively]].
